<TITLE> Youths kill one for protesting 'eve-teasing' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Apr 07 (bdnews24.com)  Garment worker Md Rakib, 22, was stabbed to death when he tried to save a colleague from a bunch of youths on Tuesday night. The incident occurred at Sagarika Loharpool area under Pahartali Police Station. Rakib was a worker at Selim and Brothers Garment factory and came from Morelganj in Bagerhat. Pankaj Dash, a sub-inspector of Chittagong Medical College (CMC) Police Station told bdnews24.com that Mohona Begum, Rakib's colleague, brought the injured Rakib to CMC Hospital on Tuesday night. She left after she had Rakib admitted to the hospital. He died at 3am. Whilst admitting her colleague to the hospital, Mohona told the police that some youths were annoying her on her way home. She said that they then stabbed Rakib when he tried to protest against their "eve-teasing". Bashir Ahmed, the acting officer of Pahartali Police Station told bdnews24.com that some youths stabbed Rakib as he protested and asked them not to disturb her. He said Rakib and Mohona were sewing operators at Selim and Brothers. They had both left the factory at around 7.15pm on Tuesday. Bashir said that Rakib's elder brother had filed a case with the Pahartali police. b
